<h1 id="set-up">Set Up</h1>
<blockquote>
  <p>Most of the following tools are recommendations. If you have any other preferences feel free to use them, but we might not be able to help you if we are unfamiliar with your environment.  If you would like an explanation, post in the Slack channel :)</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="ide">IDE</h2>
<p><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">Visual Studio Code</a> It`s free, and most customizable. You should have a look at all the awesome Visual Studio Code features, and customize your installation yourself: <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/introvideos/basics">Click me</a></p>

<h2 id="shell">Shell</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Git Bash for windows</li>
  <li>For MacOs just your normal terminal</li>
  <li>For Linux: You should be able to figure it our yourselves</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="virtual-environment">Virtual Environment</h2>
<p>We recommend <a href="https://pypi.org/project/pipenv/">Pipenv</a></p>

<h2 id="jupyterlabnotebook">Jupyterlab/Notebook</h2>
<p><a href="https://jupyter.org/">Jupyter Notebook</a></p>
